# --- YouTube auto-pull (latest videos section) ---
#
# The "Latest services & messages" section on /sermons pulls the church's
# newest uploads from the public YouTube RSS feed. No API key is required.
#
# YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_ID must be the channel's "UC..." id (NOT the @handle).
# To resolve it once: open https://www.youtube.com/@kingofglorychurch,
# View Source, and search for "channelId":"UC..." (or the /channel/UC... link).
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the value for local development.
# On the host (e.g. Vercel) set the same variable in the project's env settings.
#
# NOTE: this feature fetches live data at runtime (ISR), so the site must be
# deployed to a Node host (Vercel, etc.). It will NOT work with a static export.
YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_ID=UChFdeP6NloaOEu0cGw3tUDQ
